summary: TL* THE CONTACT OWNS A 2018 CADILLAC XT5. THE CONTACT STATED THAT THE FUEL SAFETY INDICATOR ILLUMINATED. THE VEHICLE WAS SERVICED FIVE TIMES, BUT THE FUEL SAFETY INDICATOR ILLUMINATED EVERY TIME THE VEHICLE WAS REPAIRED. THE VEHICLE WAS TAKEN TO TAYLOR CADILLAC (6100 CENTRAL AVE, TOLEDO, OH 43615, (419) 842-8800) WHERE A NEW EVAP PURGE VALVE WAS INSTALLED. SHORTLY AFTERWARDS, THE FUEL INJECTORS WERE REPLACED AND NEW ENGINE BANKS WERE INSTALLED. A FEW MONTHS AGO, THE FUEL SAFETY WARNING INDICATOR ILLUMINATED AGAIN. THE MANUFACTURER WAS MADE AWARE OF THE FAILURES AND A TECHNICIAN FROM THE MANUFACTURER WAS ASSIGNED TO INSPECT THE VEHICLE. THE FAILURE MILEAGE WAS 10,650.
